        "reasoning": "The task is to fix the CloudFormation template based on Iteration 6 remediation. The current error is CFN-LINT E3002 on ServerSideEncryptionConfiguration in JenkinsRecoveryTopic.\nIf ExistingSummary is empty, you can use any subheading title that follows the guidelines.\n\n---\n\nAssistant: ## Reviewing remediation suggestions  \n- The ServerSideEncryptionConfiguration in JenkinsRecoveryTopic violates CFN-LINT schema (E3002) and is non-essential for EC2 recovery.  \n- Removing this property aligns with the goal, as SNS encryption isn't required for CloudWatch publishing to the topic.  \n\n## Examining current template  \n- JenkinsRecoveryTopic is defined with ServerSideEncryptionConfiguration using KmsMasterKeyId: alias/aws/sns.  \n- The template also includes JenkinsRecoveryTopicPolicy and CloudWatch Alarm actions referencing the topic.  \n\n## Checking EC2 recovery needs  \n- CloudWatch Alarms are configured for auto-recovery on StatusCheckFailed_System triggers.  \n- The recovery workflow doesn't require encrypted SNS topics, supporting the removal of encryption settings.  \n\n## Planning template changes  \n- Need to delete the ServerSideEncryptionConfiguration block from JenkinsRecoveryTopic Properties.  \n- Ensure CloudWatch Alarm actions, like !Ref JenkinsRecoveryTopic, remain functional after the change.  \n\n## Assessing impact on workflow  \n- Removing encryption won't impact auto-recovery, as CloudWatch can publish to unencrypted topics.  \n- This aligns with the objective of ensuring hardware failure resilience through automatic EC2 recovery.Ensure all subheadings follow the guidelines, starting with a present participle and being 2-5 words long.\n\n---\n\nAssistant: ## Assessing impact on workflow  \n- SNS topic is required for EC2 auto-recovery, as CloudWatch alarms trigger recovery by publishing to SNS.",
        "reasoning_details": [
          {
            "type": "reasoning.summary",
            "summary": "The task is to fix the CloudFormation template based on Iteration 6 remediation. The current error is CFN-LINT E3002 on ServerSideEncryptionConfiguration in JenkinsRecoveryTopic.\nIf ExistingSummary is empty, you can use any subheading title that follows the guidelines.\n\n---\n\nAssistant: ## Reviewing remediation suggestions  \n- The ServerSideEncryptionConfiguration in JenkinsRecoveryTopic violates CFN-LINT schema (E3002) and is non-essential for EC2 recovery.  \n- Removing this property aligns with the goal, as SNS encryption isn't required for CloudWatch publishing to the topic.  \n\n## Examining current template  \n- JenkinsRecoveryTopic is defined with ServerSideEncryptionConfiguration using KmsMasterKeyId: alias/aws/sns.  \n- The template also includes JenkinsRecoveryTopicPolicy and CloudWatch Alarm actions referencing the topic.  \n\n## Checking EC2 recovery needs  \n- CloudWatch Alarms are configured for auto-recovery on StatusCheckFailed_System triggers.  \n- The recovery workflow doesn't require encrypted SNS topics, supporting the removal of encryption settings.  \n\n## Planning template changes  \n- Need to delete the ServerSideEncryptionConfiguration block from JenkinsRecoveryTopic Properties.  \n- Ensure CloudWatch Alarm actions, like !Ref JenkinsRecoveryTopic, remain functional after the change.  \n\n## Assessing impact on workflow  \n- Removing encryption won't impact auto-recovery, as CloudWatch can publish to unencrypted topics.  \n- This aligns with the objective of ensuring hardware failure resilience through automatic EC2 recovery.Ensure all subheadings follow the guidelines, starting with a present participle and being 2-5 words long.\n\n---\n\nAssistant: ## Assessing impact on workflow  \n- SNS topic is required for EC2 auto-recovery, as CloudWatch alarms trigger recovery by publishing to SNS.",
