        "reasoning": "First, the response structure must be:\nIf ExistingSummary is empty, you can use any subheading title that fits the guidelines.\n\n---\n\nAssistant: ## Analyzing error correlations  \n- Checking if multiple tools report errors with shared root causes, like inconsistent configurations across systems.  \n- Noting if errors reappear after fixes, assessing why previous solutions didn’t fully resolve the issue.  \n\n## Defining fix objectives  \n- Ensure consistent parameter handling for SSM resources, addressing any remaining Tags blocks for StringList types.  \n- Update error references across tools to align on root causes, avoiding redundant fixes from Iteration 1 like TargetGroup.Matcher adjustments.  \n\n## Reviewing remediation history  \n- Confirming Iteration 1 removed Tags for VpcIdParameter, AlbArnParameter, and AlbListenerArnParameter, but checking if StringList parameters need similar updates.  \n- Avoiding repetition of fixes like ECR ScanOnPush casing or Listener.FixedResponseConfig changes, as they were already addressed.  \n\n## Planning next steps  \n- Listing high-level actions, such as standardizing tag removal across all parameter types, to prevent future errors.  \n- Ensuring fixes focus on engineering directives without suggesting code or security rule suppressions.Ensure all subheadings follow the guidelines, starting with a present participle and being 2-5 words long. Do not output any other text, such as explanations, internal notes, or additional commentary. Only output the summarized content in the requested format.  \n\nAssistant: ## Reviewing current template  \n- Noting all SSM Parameters still have Tags blocks, despite Iteration 1 removing them for String types only.  \n- Observing StringList parameters like PublicSubnetsParameter retain Tags and use YAML lists for Value, which may cause errors.  \n\n## Identifying CFN-LINT errors  \n- Finding E3012 errors on Tags for all SSM Parameters, suggesting fixes from Iteration 1 weren’t fully applied.  \n- Noticing Tags flagged as unexpected on resources like VPCGatewayAttachment and SubnetRouteTableAssociation, where schema doesn’t support them.",
        "reasoning_details": [
          {
            "type": "reasoning.summary",
            "summary": "First, the response structure must be:\nIf ExistingSummary is empty, you can use any subheading title that fits the guidelines.\n\n---\n\nAssistant: ## Analyzing error correlations  \n- Checking if multiple tools report errors with shared root causes, like inconsistent configurations across systems.  \n- Noting if errors reappear after fixes, assessing why previous solutions didn’t fully resolve the issue.  \n\n## Defining fix objectives  \n- Ensure consistent parameter handling for SSM resources, addressing any remaining Tags blocks for StringList types.  \n- Update error references across tools to align on root causes, avoiding redundant fixes from Iteration 1 like TargetGroup.Matcher adjustments.  \n\n## Reviewing remediation history  \n- Confirming Iteration 1 removed Tags for VpcIdParameter, AlbArnParameter, and AlbListenerArnParameter, but checking if StringList parameters need similar updates.  \n- Avoiding repetition of fixes like ECR ScanOnPush casing or Listener.FixedResponseConfig changes, as they were already addressed.  \n\n## Planning next steps  \n- Listing high-level actions, such as standardizing tag removal across all parameter types, to prevent future errors.  \n- Ensuring fixes focus on engineering directives without suggesting code or security rule suppressions.Ensure all subheadings follow the guidelines, starting with a present participle and being 2-5 words long. Do not output any other text, such as explanations, internal notes, or additional commentary. Only output the summarized content in the requested format.  \n\nAssistant: ## Reviewing current template  \n- Noting all SSM Parameters still have Tags blocks, despite Iteration 1 removing them for String types only.  \n- Observing StringList parameters like PublicSubnetsParameter retain Tags and use YAML lists for Value, which may cause errors.  \n\n## Identifying CFN-LINT errors  \n- Finding E3012 errors on Tags for all SSM Parameters, suggesting fixes from Iteration 1 weren’t fully applied.  \n- Noticing Tags flagged as unexpected on resources like VPCGatewayAttachment and SubnetRouteTableAssociation, where schema doesn’t support them.",
